# Small PRs (Enforced)

## Default PR shape

- One intent per PR (one feature, bugfix, refactor, or chore).
- Prefer a “thin vertical slice”: tests → minimal implementation → cleanup.
- Keep commits small and coherent; avoid “misc fixes” bundles.

## Stop conditions (split the PR)

- The PR changes multiple unrelated areas (e.g., UI + infra + backend) without a single unifying goal.
- You can’t explain the PR in one sentence without using “and”.
- Reviewer would need to understand >1 subsystem to verify the main change.

## Practical heuristics

- If the change touches >10 files, consider splitting.
- If a new feature requires multiple acceptance criteria, ship them as separate slices unless they are inseparable.
- Prefer follow-up PRs for formatting, renames, broad refactors, dependency upgrades, or drive-by cleanup.
